comments.body:
> Could this be related to the Windows setting with path traversal?

@miketheitguy Not sure how a User Rights Assignment security setting relating to local NTFS could relate to behavior between different versions of Powershell and their interaction with a remote file share (which happens to be on a NetApp), but I'm open to any suggestions!  I have reproduced this on a different system with a user who is a local Administrator.

Are you in a position to reproduce my symptom?
